@JimToscano Thank you for coordinating everything! One last question if you can squeeze it in:

In previous webinars I remember Jonathon Nance saying that it would only take selling one of the MOBs (in Penny Farm I believe?) to pay back our capital and pref. This was one of the reasons given for being able to return capital relatively quickly in ~3 years. Now it looks from the pro-forma and newest webinar that it would actually take 3 projects to go vertical before our capital will be paid back. 

Has there been a change in thinking from CDP on this?

@FRANKSTERLING 
Did the initial mortgage have the same income sources as the refi?

Mortgage underwriting is quite opaque and common sense isn't always common but every mortgage financing transaction is an independent evaluation regardless of prior lineage. Also risk appetites and GSE regulations are changing all the time.
